caption: This is a great place to pop in and grab a slice to go while you walk around town. Staff was friendly with me and welcoming. Slices of pizza are pretty dang big.

Forgive my typos I'm using voice to text I swear I've reviewed this place before this is literally the best place you can come for pizza in Boise I honestly believe they even beat Guido's not to mention the relaxed atmosphere and more than courteous and friendly staff that you'll encounter they're taking all the precautions that they need to during the covid-19 pandemic and they have been making great food for years I first stopped in here when I was working construction before I went active duty military and I've never forgotten about this place it is truly one of my favorite spots for pizza in the whole treasure valley if y'all know any better places please let me know bye I can almost guarantee it'll be harder to find somewhere better than wise guys pizza pie

I have walked by this placed hundreds of times over the years and finally gave them a try. First off, they answered the phone! Second, they were friendly. Third, their prices were reasonable and their menu looked great. Our pizza was delivered on time and it was amazing. We ordered the wise guy and garlic knots. Both will be staples in our future orders. No they don’t offer a fancy app that lets you stalk the exact location of your delivery but it is honest, quality pizza at an affordable price. Highly recommended. We will be sure to support on a regular basis!

How you measure the quality of service is not when it's normal, but when they make a mistake. They forgot a slice on our order, which makes sense since they were slammed, normaly this would lead to extra hassle of getting back in line and getting another. This didnt happen, instead, no questions asked, they gave me 2 on the house. That is the service you would get at a 5 star restaurant, and you get it here. Curtis is the man.

Placed my order at 5:52.  At 7:15 I called to see if something had gone wrong.  Turns out, they had simply not noticed my order was waiting for delivery.  I asked that the food be made fresh and sent out.  I was assured it would be.  It arrived 20 minutes later and the wings were room temperature.  They offered a refund, but their incompetence was such that I honestly didn't want them interacting with my bank account any more than they already had.  I have had many great experiences with Wise Guys in the past and am sadly disappointed that I will not have any in the future.

Given that this is the only pizza place we have returned to multiple times, in our first year in Boise, it is potentially the best one we have found so far. Like their pizzas; they have very good specialty pizzas; no reason to build out own. We liked the Sad Guy yesterday! No information on site nor leaflet about opening and delivery times. Feels a bit like 'whenever we feel like it'.

Taste preferences in pizza are a very regional thing. If you are from the east coast, you will like Wiseguy as a New York style pizza. The ingredients are fresh/high quality so it beats Pie Hole and Guido's.  Most of what Idaho offers in pizza is horrible. If you're raised on dog food, you think dog food is good.  Many locals like a bread-like crust and lacking/tasteless sauce.  You can get that at Smokey Mountain, Idaho Pizza Co, Flying Pie, and other local chains. There are other "artisan" pizza choices which can be tasty but you don't get much and most of the time I want a pizza with traditional toppings.  I have tried them all in Boise, lived all over the USA, and as an accused pizza snob, Wiseguy is in the top % for Boise.
Great Pizza
Horrible customer services on the phone.

Great Pizza. I didn't experience anything bad about this place like other reviewers. The service was great and the food was amazing. We stopped in for lunch after seeing the pizza in the window. I'll be back.

Avoid Wiseguy Pizza!....Terrible pizza the last time I went in, but decided to give them another try, but it was horrible, horrible, this is from my experience last summer....lots, lots and lots of flies all over the pizzas in the storefront "by the slice" area, and, when asked about why so many flies, the unfriendly gal behind the counter said there is nothing she could do about it, when we asked other staff in the restaurant in back, they could care less, and said they could not do anything about it.  When she reached in to grab a slice for another customer, a large number of flies dispersed into the air, it was DISGUSTING, so we left and went to Guido's instead, please go to Guido's instead, you will be much happier!

I have been a big fan ever since they moved into the valley.  The service is great and the garlic knots are amazing.  My favorite pie is the fat hot Hawaiian.  It is ham, pineapple, bacon and jalapeño. They have a constantly rotating beer selection but always have vitamin R on tap.  Slices are always available even late. Very kid friendly.  High chairs and boosters available.  There is also outside seating.

I seriously think the employees should get different jobs. I felt as though they hate customers, and I don't see myself going back here. Too bad. I can be contacted by anyone for a more detailed description of events. I love the pizza at Piehole..
Huge slices and a decent top menu. They have traditional as well as non-traditional types of pizza.

The owner is a JERK to put it nicely! My husband I went into Wiseguy's and asked if we could buy just two waters. He handed me back my card and said no charge which I thought was very nice! We looked around the restaurant and noticed that there was only about five people total in the restaurant we took a seat at a back table and began discussing what slice of pizza we wanted (even though we weren't hungry) we wanted to buy something because he gave us the free waters. Not even five minutes after sitting down the owner came over and slammed down a menu on our table and said "this is not a charity, order something or get out!" He went on for probably five more minutes before my husband interrupted him and said okay we get it we will get out. During his rant I couldn't help but mention the beer in his hand which might have had something to do with his wildly inappropriate behavior! I have been a waitress and I understand that if the restaurant is full you don't sit down and take a table that someone who is buying food can use. However, there were only four people in the restaurant total so I didn't think the owner would mind. I will NEVER go back to this place again and I encourage all my friends not to support a business with an owner that was so rude to his potential customers.

This is a great place to grab a slice and have a beer, or stop in for a more sit-down dinner.  Located in the heart of downtown they offer quite a bit of seating inside and have a patio area outside as well.  Our personal favorite is the Pestotarian which is more of a Mediterranean flavor but really works very well!  Check it out, you wont be disappointed.

I don't eat gluten and I don't really like the 'standard' gluten free pizza crust that everyone buys from the same place. Wiseguy get's their crust made from an Idaho company and it's actually good. Their topping combinations are amazing and their wings have been safe for me as well. I really like this place when it comes to pizza that we don't make at home.

We've been fans of Guidos for a long time - unfortunately, so is everyone else.  We stumbled across Wiseguy Pizza when Guidos estimated a 60 minute prep time.  Wiseguy's makes a great pizza, they are fast, friendly and they have a great location - right on Main Street.  You'll not be sorry you dropped in or ordered out!
Never disapointed. I love that they stay open so late.  Worth the drive from Nampa.

Let me start by saying the experience only deserves 3 stars because the crust is solid.  Beyond that, what a disappointment!  We've ordered specialty pizzas from this shop 3-4 times prior and were disappointed in the execution with the toppings, but we ordered the Margarita Guy this time around thinking August in Boise would guarantee a good product.  Wrong.  Tomatoes were flavorless, obviously commercial, and not even remotely covered the pie although we're right in the middle of tomato season.  Basil was lacking and added little.  Overall, a flavorless pizza.  This is especially disappointing because other NY style pizza shops (Guido's for one) would charge half the price with twice the flavor on essentially the same pizza.  Wiseguy:  wake up and realize you are a small Idaho business in the middle of summer!  Even without dropping your ridiculous prices, you could take advantage of the local food movement, get amazing produce to feature on popular pies and KILL IT!  Please do.  We'd love to make you our go-to pizza delivery spot, but you've got to try a little harder than that.
Pizza fantiastic.  Wings is the best kept secret.  Management does a great job of picking very good beer and wine.  The DECK is the best place in town for people watching and playing cornhole
If you like New York style pizza and are considering these guys, Pie Hole, and Guido's,  come here for the heartiest pizza.   They deliver for lunch as well.

So I am a total New York pizza snob and have very high standards...Wiseguys is really good and right up there with some of the best pizza in Boise! For my money, it's Wiseguys and Guido's and everything else is a few tiers down.  Went on Friday night before a basketball game and ordered a large pizza and some wings. The pizza came and was fantastic...crisp crust with a bit of a crunch, nice balance of cheese and toppings...really good!  They didn't catch our wings when we ordered them, so when my son asked about them they brought us an order and didn't charge us for them...very good service!  Looking forward to many a pies at this place!

A few of us from work go out for pizza at lunch every Friday, after three years, we're quite familiar with every pizza joint in Boise. Wise Guys popped up on our radar a while back and it's now one of two favorites pizza places in Boise. If you want fancy Italian gourmet pizza go just down the street to our other favorite "Flat Bread" but if you're in the mood for good old fashioned Americanized pizza or pizza by the slice.... you absolutely must try Wise Guy's. For thin crust, their crust has a lot of character and flavor. They have two counters; up front they have pizza by the slice, in back a full pizzeria menu. And as you'll see in other reviews, the service is excellent.
